  "text": "SPARK is a formally defined subset of the ADA programming language [CITATION_1] . It was motivated by the need for developing software for high reliability and safety critical applications. The SPARK language consists of a welldefined subset of the ADA language and property specifications. The properties are specified as program annotations, inline with the source code and embedded as ADA comments. As a subset of ADA, SPARK programs can be compiled by any ADA compiler.",
